## Block E — Security Hardening (remaining 20%)

### Step E1: Origin/CSRF check on AI POST routes

> **What:** Reject AI API requests that don't originate from your own domain.

#### [NEW] [origin-guard.ts](file:///c:/Users/jabbo/M1plan/planevo/apps/web/lib/auth/origin-guard.ts)

Create a reusable helper:
```typescript
// Checks the Origin or Referer header against allowed origins.
// Returns true if the request is safe, false if it should be blocked.
export function isAllowedOrigin(request: NextRequest): boolean
```
- Reads `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` from env (e.g. `https://planevo.app`)
- In development, also allows `http://localhost:3000`
- Checks `Origin` header first, falls back to `Referer`
- Returns `false` (and logs a warning) if neither matches

#### [MODIFY] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/jabbo/M1plan/planevo/apps/web/app/api/ai/chat/route.ts)

- Import `isAllowedOrigin` at the top
- Add a 3-line guard **before** the rate limit check:
  ```
  if (!isAllowedOrigin(request)) return 403 "Forbidden: invalid origin"
  ```

#### [MODIFY] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/jabbo/M1plan/planevo/apps/web/app/api/ai/daily-plan/route.ts)

- Same 3-line guard added at the top of the `POST` handler.

#### [MODIFY] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/jabbo/M1plan/planevo/apps/web/app/api/ai/weekly-review/route.ts)

- Same guard. Additionally add an exemption: if the request contains a `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` header, skip the origin check (needed for Step G1's cron trigger).

